history.content:
Low workload is a hard requirement to fulfill, but you can consider Stat 134 or Stat 140 (if you meet the prereqs, Adhikari is a fantastic instructor).

Other options could be EECS 106A, EECS 149..

If you have some interest in EE, look at @6645.

-------

BTW, I believe Stat 134 or 140 is only considered low workload if you do well in 70.

history.content: Hey all, I need to take a non-COMPSCI (can be pure EECS though, no cross listings) tech elective to fulfill all requirements in order to graduate next Fall, and I'm looking for some recommendations. I've gone over the tech elective list, and nothing caught my eye :/ Currently, I intend on taking EECS 126 along with 161, 162, 168, but that's probably too much. Ideally, it would be a class with a great instructor and low workload, so any suggestions? :)
